fr.sorbonne_u.components.examples.basic_cs.interfaces

Interface URIConsumerI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ComponentServiceI, RequiredI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    URIConsumerOutboundPort, URIServiceConnector

    public interface URIConsumerI
extends RequiredI
    The interface URIConsumerI defines the interface required by a component that needs to get URI from an URI provider component.

    Description

    As a RMI remote interface, all of the methods must return RemoteException. The choice here is to throw Exception to cater for potential exceptions thrown by the implementation methods.

    Created on : 2014-01-22

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
